article.description: LaQuita Owens scored 22 points and grabbed seven rebounds to help No. 12 West Virginia roll past Georgetown 67-35 on Saturday.
article.headline: Owens' 22 key No. 12 West Virginia's rout of Georgetown
article.linkText: Owens helps West Virginia roll past Georgetown
article.story:
MORGANTOWN, W.Va. (AP) -- LaQuita Owens scored 22 points and grabbed seven rebounds to help No. 12 West Virginia roll past Georgetown 67-35 on Saturday.

The Mountaineers (16-3, 5-1 Big East) won despite the absence of Meg Bulger, who tweaked her surgically repaired left knee during West Virginia's win over Marshall on Wednesday.

Ashley Powell, Liz Repellea and Olayinka Sanni scored nine points apiece to help pace the Mountaineers.

West Virginia raced to a 40-20 lead in the first half on the strength of a 16-3 run midway through the period. West Virginia shot 60.7 percent in the half, while holding Georgetown (11-8, 1-5) to nine field goals and 32 percent from the floor.

Monica McNutt scored 13 to lead Georgetown.

West Virginia's lead ballooned to 35 in the second half and Georgetown never threatened as the Hoyas shot just 30 percent from the field.

West Virginia will host No. 5 Rutgers on Tuesday night.
